      "content": "okay that makes sense for the economic side. but to really nail this debate i need to get deeper into the logic people used to justify the actual racial aspect of it. like, some people back then argued that keeping different racial groups in specific areas was actually good for preventing \"social friction\" or maintaining cultural cohesion within communities. can u help me flesh out that specific argument? i need to understand the \"logic\" of how segregation was presented as a way to protect cultural identity or prevent conflict, so i can respond to it during the debate.",
